1
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:09,280
Welcome to the most beloved
game show!

2
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:12,200
It's The Big Challenge!

3
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:12,200
Please welcome our next contestant!

4
00:00:14,519 --> 00:00:19,840
All right, Nino, both our student
and...

5
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:21,240
This is truly something great.

6
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:24,000
Would you like to take a look
at the system we've prepared for you?

7
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:26,840
Am I in detention? But why?

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:30,359
Rack your brain a little, Marinette.
You were absent Monday morning class.

9
00:00:31,560 --> 00:00:37,680
I was in the study hall.

10
00:00:34,360 --> 00:00:37,680
You weren't in the study hall
Friday afternoon either.

11
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:44,120
Right, I was in gym class.

12
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:46,879
You can never be where
you're supposed to be.

13
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:49,559
The only way for us to know where you are
is for you to stay here.

14
00:00:46,879 --> 00:00:51,640
You're in detention.
But I had invited Nino —

15
00:00:49,559 --> 00:00:53,840
my friend was counting on me.

16
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:58,920
Our audience has selected
your challenge:

17
00:00:53,840 --> 00:01:01,079
Paris Mayor André Bourgeois.

18
00:00:58,920 --> 00:01:02,680
Thank you for joining us, sir.
Do you think Nino has a chance?

19
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:07,080
Zero. I hate dancing.
The last time I was on a dance floor,

20
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:11,920
Madonna was still a baby, kid.

21
00:01:09,479 --> 00:01:14,960
Nino is your friend, I know,
but as long as these unexplained

22
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:16,750
disappearances continue,
things can't go on like this.

23
00:01:23,119 --> 00:01:28,240
Great. Are they wrong though?

24
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:30,640
How could they know you're skipping class
to save the world?

25
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:32,640
Being a superhero in secret
means getting detention at school too.

26
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:37,200
But I don't think it's fair —
it's just not right.

27
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:39,479
But look, if Nino wins,
you won't be in detention next week —

28
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:43,759
you can go and watch him.

29
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:43,759
Yeah, but Adrien was there today.

30
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:51,439
The Big Challenge... What an
interesting show.

31
00:01:49,119 --> 00:01:53,079
A program where negative emotions
can come into play.

32
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:57,280
So many bad things could happen.

33
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:02,320
Are you serious? How can you say that, Alya?

34
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:04,320
I'm sorry, but I understand
your father, Marinette.

35
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:06,119
You're never where you say you'll be,
you're always late,

36
00:02:06,119 --> 00:02:10,280
you mysteriously disappear somewhere.

37
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:14,040
It's almost like you have another life.

38
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:16,880
Come on, Alya, you're being a bit silly,
please.

39
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:18,680
Wait here.

40
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:27,200
No problem.

41
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:29,040
Victory! Nino succeeded in his challenge.

42
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:31,239
You were nodding your head to the beat —
anything else?

43
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:33,640
That counts as dancing too.

44
00:02:31,239 --> 00:02:36,120
What? That's not right.

45
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:37,680
Well, my neck was itchy,
that's all. That's it.

46
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:40,400
Scratching your neck to the rhythm
of the music is also a dance.

47
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:42,239
Nino, congratulations.

48
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:44,640
You'll be back here next week
for your next challenge.

49
00:02:42,239 --> 00:02:47,519
And now our next contestant is coming up.

50
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:51,480
Welcome, Simon Grimault.

51
00:02:47,519 --> 00:02:53,599
That was amazing, dude!

52
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:55,159
Hey Grimault. You hypnotize people
with cards and make them do

53
00:02:53,599 --> 00:02:58,440
whatever you want, right?

54
00:02:55,159 --> 00:03:01,599
Sure. Yes, I'm a hypnotist, but I can't
make a living from this talent.

55
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:05,959
And today's challenge:
Simon will use his abilities

56
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:08,120
to convince an unwilling star
to come onstage.

57
00:03:05,959 --> 00:03:12,239
Now let's hear everyone's applause!

58
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:15,239
Gabriel Agreste!

59
00:03:12,239 --> 00:03:17,840
What kind of show is this?
I was told I'd be giving an interview, man.

60
00:03:15,239 --> 00:03:19,640
Show your trick, Grimault.
Let's see if you can use your hypnosis

61
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:22,200
to convince Mr. Agreste
to come onstage.

62
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:24,840
I told you, I'm a shy hypnotist.

63
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:28,080
What does that make you?

64
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:31,120
Interesting, isn't it, Gabriel?
Very funny.

65
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:32,319
The show is terrible,
and so are the contestants.

66
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:35,879
Hypnosis? Never.

67
00:03:32,319 --> 00:03:38,159
This is my father.

68
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:41,239
That's right. It seems Mr. Agreste
is refusing the challenge.

69
00:03:38,159 --> 00:03:43,760
Game over.

70
00:03:41,239 --> 00:03:43,760
But this is unfair!
You didn't even give me a chance!

71
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:55,319
Yes, humiliation and anger are the very factors
that can turn a loser into a winner.

72
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:14,000
Fly, my little akuma,
and infect him with evil.

73
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:21,959
I am Hawk Moth. From now on,
your name is Simon Says.

74
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:25,240
I will make you the world's
most successful hypnotist.

75
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:27,919
And when the time comes,
you will help me in return.

76
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:33,320
Of course, what do you say?
Do we have a deal?

77
00:04:27,919 --> 00:04:33,320
Simon Says... Simon says yes.

78
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:42,039
Simon says the show isn't over yet.

79
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:45,720
What's going on?

80
00:04:42,039 --> 00:04:45,720
Silence! You're all pathetic.
You're all chickens.

81
00:04:50,800 --> 00:05:00,479
Simon says stop!

82
00:04:54,240 --> 00:05:00,479
Simon says act like pigs!

83
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:17,000
I have to go, Alya. Have fun.

84
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:19,520
I'll babysit now, Tikki.

85
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:22,960
What am I going to do?
I'm in detention.

86
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:28,520
You have no choice, you have to transform.
But we need to be more careful.

87
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:28,520
Take the pillow from under the blanket.

88
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:35,199
Not bad.

89
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:35,199
Tikki? Spots on!

90
00:05:58,639 --> 00:06:05,680
Gabriel Agreste refused my challenge.

91
00:06:02,639 --> 00:06:07,800
He'll pay for it. Tonight at midnight
he'll be entertaining us all in this studio.

92
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:14,039
Gabriel, I'm coming for you, father.

93
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:17,160
Too risky. But I have an idea.
Good luck.

94
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:29,240
Simon Says: Give me those cards
and be quiet, Cat Noir.

95
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:34,520
I'll deal with you.

96
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:37,480
Simon says drive everyone away!

97
00:06:37,759 --> 00:06:43,360
Even if I don't always land
on all fours, I always bounce back.

98
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:50,960
Should I have an army?

99
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:57,919
Simon says: You are all soldiers!

100
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:07,680
Simon says: Search all of Paris!

101
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,680
My army, find Gabriel Agreste!

102
00:07:12,199 --> 00:07:19,680
We need to be careful. As you taught me,
size doesn't matter.

103
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:27,160
Ladybug, hello. Are you okay?

104
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:30,879
I'm fine, but my friend is
somewhere inside. I'll find him.

105
00:07:30,879 --> 00:07:35,680
Cataclysm!

106
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:39,479
Hello, Ladybug.

107
00:07:43,759 --> 00:07:52,350
That's enough! Cataclysm!

108
00:08:01,319 --> 00:08:06,560
Good to see you too, Cat Noir.
Sorry, I mistook you for Simon Says.

109
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:10,879
I saw him — he has a massive army with him.

110
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:13,080
He must be after Gabriel.
We need to reach him before the army does.

111
00:08:10,879 --> 00:08:15,280
Cat Noir, you're about to transform back.

112
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:17,360
Let me check on Nino's friends
one last time.

113
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:19,680
Forget it, they've definitely been hypnotized.

114
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:22,159
But he's my friend.

115
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:24,479
You're right, maybe he can hide.
You go look for him.

116
00:08:22,159 --> 00:08:26,879
Then let's meet at Gabriel's house.

117
00:08:24,479 --> 00:08:26,879
See you there.

118
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:31,440
Finding him will be child's play.

119
00:08:36,479 --> 00:08:39,760
Claws out! Hide, Nino!

120
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:47,880
Adrien! Buddy, are you okay?

121
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:52,040
I'm fine.

122
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:55,000
Hello? Hello? Are you really okay?

123
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:57,800
I'm fine, really. But we need to go
to my house right away —

124
00:08:55,000 --> 00:09:01,440
my father is in danger!
Let's go, we'll meet Cat Noir there.

125
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:09,959
Nathalie! Where's my father?
He's in trouble. He already knows.

126
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:12,240
Good evening, Ladybug.

127
00:09:09,959 --> 00:09:14,240
Dad, you need to leave —
the hypnotist Simon Says is after you.

128
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:17,160
What? Should I run from a madman? Never.

129
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:19,160
But father, he's very dangerous —
who knows what he might do to you!

130
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:21,120
Go to your room now,
you've had enough excitement for today.

131
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:25,959
Nathalie, make sure
they don't go outside.

132
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:28,680
I apologize on behalf of my son, Ladybug.

133
00:09:25,959 --> 00:09:31,680
He's just like his mother —
a bit too dramatic.

134
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:34,279
But he's quite right too.
Simon Says is dangerous —

135
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:37,680
you're in danger as well.

136
00:09:34,279 --> 00:09:39,680
With you here protecting me,
what could possibly happen to me?

137
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:43,880
Are you sure your father
isn't some kind of robot?

138
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:43,880
According to him,
I understand nothing about anything.

139
00:09:45,399 --> 00:09:50,720
Dude, your room is bigger
than a small stadium.

140
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:53,480
Please make yourself comfortable —
I'm going to take a shower.

141
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:56,200
Right now? What can I say —

142
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:58,680
I'm a model.

143
00:09:56,200 --> 00:10:01,320
Why does my father never listen to me?

144
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:29,640
Claws out! How perfect...

145
00:10:27,079 --> 00:10:34,399
What? I don't understand —
my son is a perfect child, isn't he?

146
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:36,279
Yes, perfect. I mean, I don't know him
very well, but it seems that...

147
00:10:34,399 --> 00:10:39,120
I noticed your earrings before —
they're really quite fascinating.

148
00:10:36,279 --> 00:10:42,800
May I take a look?

149
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:49,480
Excuse me. Cat Noir! Where were you?

150
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:53,279
I... I was keeping Simon Says busy.

151
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:55,959
And Cat Noir — I couldn't hold him off for long.

152
00:10:53,279 --> 00:10:55,959
He's on his way and there's a huge crowd.

153
00:10:57,040 --> 00:11:01,600
Seal all the exits —
they're coming from every direction.

154
00:10:59,839 --> 00:11:05,279
Do as I say —
activate the defense systems.

155
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:05,279
Everything must be locked down.

156
00:11:07,079 --> 00:11:10,880
Lockdown successful.

157
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:18,160
How do you know this system so well?
In a house like this? I guessed.

158
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:22,800
They can't get in —
this house is as solid as a fortress.

159
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:29,519
Simon says: Destroy it!

160
00:11:38,639 --> 00:11:44,760
The strain is too much.
The system won't hold.

161
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:51,079
Seal the entrances and exits —
we'll operate the controls together here if needed.

162
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:52,880
I'll help with the outer defense.
You hide somewhere.

163
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:56,279
This place is safe.

164
00:11:59,639 --> 00:12:06,370
Stop telling me what to do!
Just do what I say!

165
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:09,419
Pretty grumpy. Reminds me of someone.

166
00:12:19,199 --> 00:12:24,600
I don't think this is a good idea.

167
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:27,839
Simon Says: "Gabriel is here."

168
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:30,839
Yes, but don't forget our deal.

169
00:12:27,839 --> 00:12:33,399
Ladybug and Cat Noir should be nearby.

170
00:12:30,839 --> 00:12:35,639
When you face them,
fulfill our agreement —

171
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:38,600
take their jewelry,
their Miraculouses.

172
00:12:35,639 --> 00:12:40,160
It will finally be over.

173
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:43,279
Simon says: I will defeat them!

174
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:45,560
Ladybug, what's going on?

175
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:49,279
Let's move somewhere safer.
Where's Adrien?

176
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:52,560
He was taking a shower.

177
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:57,160
Right now? Well, he is a model.

178
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:57,160
Take Nino to the garden —
I'll handle Adrien. Leave the remote with me.

179
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:06,800
Adrien?

180
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:12,560
Yes? Maybe we should go?
It's dangerous — very dangerous.

181
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:15,760
Can I get dressed first?

182
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:18,600
Of course, go ahead.
Sure, sure, get dressed and we can go.

183
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:28,420
Absolutely. Where's my son?
He's coming — he's with Ladybug.

184
00:13:33,639 --> 00:13:41,920
Ha! This is my mother —
on her 17th birthday. She was a beautiful woman.

185
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:41,920
You have the same eyes.

186
00:13:46,279 --> 00:13:53,720
Stay here. Oh, what's all this?
Is this love or something?

187
00:13:53,720 --> 00:14:01,040
Ha? What do you say?
I need to help.

188
00:13:56,759 --> 00:14:01,040
Claws out!

189
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,199
Are they coming again?

190
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:22,779
I've got you, Cat Noir!

191
00:14:29,839 --> 00:14:32,920
Yes, that was great.

192
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:38,279
Welcome to the new episode of The Big Challenge!

193
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:41,560
Hello everyone again — I'm Simon Says.

194
00:14:38,279 --> 00:14:43,440
Audience, I kept my promise —

195
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:48,519
here is Gabriel!

196
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:48,519
Simon says: You are a butterfly!

197
00:14:50,759 --> 00:14:58,040
Fly, fly, fly, fly!
Come on, fly!

198
00:14:54,360 --> 00:15:02,040
Fly! We have to save Mr. Agreste.

199
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:04,079
Butterfly, I'm going to destroy you now.

200
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:07,600
The akuma must be in one of those cards —
but which one?

201
00:15:04,079 --> 00:15:07,600
There are so many of them!

202
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:15,560
Ladybug, Cat Noir —
give me your Miraculouses

203
00:15:13,199 --> 00:15:20,839
and he can be saved. Now give up!

204
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:20,839
In your dreams. Lucky Charm!

205
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:29,839
Just a yo-yo? But I thought
it had some magical use.

206
00:15:26,839 --> 00:15:32,720
We can figure that out later. Ha?

207
00:15:29,839 --> 00:15:35,849
Simon says: Your yo-yo is useless!

208
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:48,079
Simon Says: "Your staff
is useless too?" I don't think so.

209
00:15:48,079 --> 00:15:51,399
I won't give you any more chances to speak.

210
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:17,199
Simon Says.

211
00:16:18,730 --> 00:16:22,519
Fly, come on, fly!

212
00:16:22,519 --> 00:16:27,440
He's heading for the roof —
we have to stop him.

213
00:16:29,319 --> 00:16:33,480
I can't do this alone.

214
00:16:31,079 --> 00:16:35,279
If we can free Simon,
we can save Mr. Agreste too.

215
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:37,480
Then we can't waste any more time.

216
00:16:35,279 --> 00:16:40,160
But without my yo-yo —
how are you going to beat him?

217
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:46,240
Simon says: It's over!

218
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,680
Follow me.

219
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,640
Cataclysm!

220
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:19,679
Miraculous Ladybug!

221
00:17:19,679 --> 00:17:23,270
This can't be — the yo-yo wasn't working.

222
00:17:19,679 --> 00:17:23,270
That one wasn't. But this one works.

223
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:41,440
Yo-yo! You won't be able to do
any more evil, little akuma!

224
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:45,360
Bye bye, little butterfly.

225
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:51,590
Pound it!

246
00:17:54,679 --> 00:18:01,280
Fist bump! Seems your touch
sensor stopped working.

247
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:07,320
Sir, if you were my Ladybug...

248
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:10,679
Actually, Cat Noir, you're not wrong.
Your face...

249
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:14,120
You'd better leave now.
Running away like a cat on a rooftop.

250
00:18:10,679 --> 00:18:14,120
Until we meet again,
Mr. Agreste.

251
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:23,120
We'll see you too.

252
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:53,679
I've never seen your face before.

253
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:56,120
That's because there's a lot about me
you haven't noticed.

254
00:18:56,120 --> 00:19:12,120
I'm so glad everything worked out.

255
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:16,440
Welcome back to the number one
game show!

256
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:18,240
It's The Big Challenge!

257
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:20,039
Last week our DJ friend Nino
completed the big challenge.

258
00:19:20,039 --> 00:19:25,200
Now we're hearing from him again.
Come on up, DJ!

259
00:19:29,679 --> 00:19:35,159
It looks like you haven't
been late at all this week, my boy.

260
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:37,679
That's wonderful — well done.

261
00:19:35,159 --> 00:19:41,240
You can join your friends on set.

262
00:19:37,679 --> 00:19:43,280
I'd rather watch from here.
Mom won't mind, I think.

263
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:49,000
Tonight the challenge level
has been raised a bit.

264
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:52,000
Nino will need to make not one
but two celebrities dance.

265
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:55,240
But now you get to choose who.

266
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:57,760
This should be a cinch —
I'll choose two people

267
00:19:55,240 --> 00:20:02,240
I think won't turn me down:

268
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:06,880
Ladybug and Cat Noir.

269
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:09,640
Actually, I'm a bit tired — I should catch some sleep
so I won't be late for school tomorrow.

270
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:13,679
And after all, I shouldn't let my grades slip.

271
00:20:13,679 --> 00:20:17,120
You'll fill me in, of course, darling.

272
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:22,159
I honestly don't understand
that girl sometimes.

273
00:20:20,559 --> 00:20:25,919
But we'd better not push it.
There's nothing harder than going to school,

274
00:20:22,159 --> 00:20:25,919
as you know.
